Description: Scott Cooper Miami works hard to bring you the latest news, insights, and analysis about education in Miami and Florida.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: At Scott Cooper Miami, we believe that education is the key to building a brighter, more prosperous future for all. So, we work hard to bring you the latest news, insights, and analysis about education in Miami and Florida. From breaking news to in-depth features, interviews with education leaders, and analysis of education policy, our team of experienced journalists, educators, and researchers is here to bring you the stories that matter most. We cover a wide range of topics, from classroom innovations to funding challenges, and we're committed to promoting access, equity, and excellence in education for all students. But we don't stop there. We also provide resources and tips for parents, students, and educators on everything from college admissions to classroom management. Our goal is to help you make informed decisions about education policy, funding, and innovation, and to provide you with the tools you need to support your children's education. At Scott Cooper Miami, we believe in the power of education to transform lives and communities. We are passionate about promoting critical thinking, creativity, and innovation in education, and we're dedicated to promoting a culture of learning, curiosity, and intellectual engagement. We also think that diversity, fairness, and inclusion are important in education, and we're committed to promoting these values in everything we do. Our team comes from diverse backgrounds and brings a wide range of perspectives to our reporting. Our partnerships with local schools, universities, and education organizations help us to provide you with access to the latest research, best practices, and innovative programs in education. We also work with community groups, advocacy groups, and policymakers to make sure that all students have access to an excellent education that is also fair and equal. So if you're looking for a reliable source of education news and information in Miami and Florida, look no further than Scott Cooper Miami. Follow us on social media, sign up for our newsletter, and join the conversation on the issues that matter most to you. We're here to help you stay informed, involved, and motivated on your journey to support education in Miami and Florida.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: There are over 3.3 billion women living in the world today. Yet if you judge solely by the mainstream media you might conclude those 3.3 billion people are less intelligent, less articulate, less funny, have less to say about issues (even those directly affecting them) or perhaps only make up 5 to 30% of the population. Of course, none of that is true. What is true is that women have less opportunity to contribute to conversations, because they are less likely to own media, be asked for their opinion regardless of their qualifications, be published or be given the chance to tell their story. At Women, Action and the Media (WAM!) we think that needs to change and we know how to make it happen. We are an independent, non-profit organization building a robust, effective, inclusive movement for gender justice in the media. We are also a strong, growing community of people engaged with media, learning and sharing capacity and skills needed to build a media ecosystem that represents the diversity of our lives and stories.

Description: TiterMax adjuvants are used to produce cell mediated and humoral responses in research animals.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: TiterMax adjuvants are used to produce cell mediated and humoral responses in research animals.  TiterMax adjuvants were developed to meet the specific needs of investigators for immunoadjuvants that are at least as effective as Freund's Complete Adjuvant, safer and easier to use. They are an attractive alternative to Freund's Complete Adjuvant for use by researchers in inducing antibody to diverse antigens. The key to the potency of TiterMax adjuvants lies both in the immunostimulatory activity of their components and in the fact that they form a stable water-in-oil emulsion. TiterMax adjuvants contain three essential ingredients: Proprietary block copolymers, squalene, a metabolizable oil, and a unique microparticulate stabilizer. Like Freund's Complete Adjuvant, TiterMax adjuvants can be used with a wide variety of antigens because they can entrap any antigen in a water-in-oil emulsion.  TiterMax adjuvants aid in the antigens effective presentation to the immune system without the toxic effects of Freund's Complete Adjuvant. TiterMax is a registered trademark of TiterMax USA, Inc.
